<strong>----- English -----</strong><br>
<br>
Dear teacher,<br>
<br>
In 3 days your digital exam for the course @{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['field_6']}
(@{items('Apply_to_each_-_send_e-mails')?['field_7']}) will take place.<br>
<br>
<strong>What can I expect?</strong><br>
There will be at least one room-coordinator and assistant floor manager (AFM'er) present on site, please introduce yourself to them on arrival. Before the exam starts, the AFM'er will walk you through the exam to confirm everything is set up correctly. Please arrive at the exam location <u>1 hour to 45 minutes prior to the start</u> of the exam to ensure this final check can be performed. After this, you'll only have to be present to assist students with questions related to the contents of the exam. The AFM'er(s) will ensure the technical aspects of the exam are configured properly. The exam is password protected, so students will only be able to access the exam once they enter the password. The AFM'er will share the password with the students when it is time to start the exam.<br>
<br>
<strong>Anything I can do?</strong><br>
Share <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/28129/pages/digital-exams-faq-students">this page</a> with your students. This page contains an FAQ for students and instructions on how to log in to TestVision at the exam location. On the <a href="https://canvas.uva.nl/courses/28129/pages/digital-exams-faq-students">FAQ for teachers</a> you will find the most important information regarding moment of examination. Should you have any further questions, please send us an e-mail.<br>
<br>
